The paper discusses the use of data provenance methods to increase transparency and accountability in complex systems, with a focus on algorithmic decision-making. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories, including cs.CR (security and privacy), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.DB (databases), cs.SE (software engineering), and cs.LG (machine learning). However, given the emphasis on accountability and oversight, cs.CR is the most likely category, followed by cs.AI and cs.DB.
